[src:rosetta-code/100-doors-p05] The solution consists in having a 100 element array, initialized with FALSE values.
[src:rosetta-code/100-doors-p05] In each of the 100 rounds (controlled by a simple FOR-FROM-TO cycle), the values are flipped using a FOR-FROM-TO-STEP cycle.
[src:rosetta-code/100-doors-p05] Finally the array is shown, using green colors for open doors, and red for closed ones.
[src:rosetta-code/100-doors-p05] The resulting matrix is transposed in order to be shown horizontally.
[src:rosetta-code/100-doors-p05] The 100 doors problem reduces to finding perfect squares from 1 to 100, since only doors at perfect square positions remain open.
