[src:rosetta-code/binary-search-p01] The following algorithms return the rightmost place where the given element can be correctly inserted (and still maintain the sorted order).
[src:rosetta-code/binary-search-p01] This is the upper (exclusive) bound of the range of elements that are equal to the given value (if any).
[src:rosetta-code/binary-search-p01] Equivalently, this is the lowest index where the element is greater than the given value, or 1 past the last index if such an element does not exist.
[src:rosetta-code/binary-search-p01] Note that these algorithms are almost exactly the same as the leftmost-insertion-point algorithms, except for how the inequality treats equal values.
