[src:rosetta-code/dining-philosophers-p01] Pythagoras is pondering about how many straws makes a bale. . . . .
[src:rosetta-code/dining-philosophers-p01] Uses C++14 Without threads, uses state machine.
[src:rosetta-code/dining-philosophers-p01] Clojure's STM allows us to avoid low-level synchronization primitives like semaphores.
[src:rosetta-code/dining-philosophers-p01] In order to simulate the Dining Philosophers scenario, the forks are references to a boolean indicating whether or not it is available for use.
[src:rosetta-code/dining-philosophers-p01] The second line of the start-eating function contains the essential solution: by invoking ensure on every fork reference, we are guaranteed that the state of the forks will not be modified by other transactions, thus we can rely on those values for the rest of the transaction.
[src:rosetta-code/dining-philosophers-p01] The status function inspects the data structures within a transaction so as to give consistent results (e.g., every unavailable fork has exactly one "eating" philosopher adjacent).
