[src:rosetta-code/dining-philosophers-p04] From this implementation's point of view, a "resource" is not a *fork*, but rather a *place at the table*.
[src:rosetta-code/dining-philosophers-p04] Rather than use one `MUTEX` for *each* fork, it uses one `MUTEX` for the entire table.
[src:rosetta-code/dining-philosophers-p04] It is easy to modify this so that each philosopher does not rise from the table, but eats and thinks only at his assigned place.
[src:rosetta-code/dining-philosophers-p04] In fact, the original implementation did precisely that, but when I saw that some implementations allowed the philosophers to sit at any place with two available forks, I opted for that.
[src:rosetta-code/dining-philosophers-p04] While this implementation is not a translation of the Eiffel solution, it still owes it a heads-up for the basic principle.
