[src:rosetta-code/fibonacci-sequence-p06] The predicate `main/2` illustrates first the unification semantics of the predicate form and the function call semantics of the function form.
[src:rosetta-code/fibonacci-sequence-p06] The provided code uses a very naive form of generating a Fibonacci number.
[src:rosetta-code/fibonacci-sequence-p06] A more realistic implementation would use memoization to cache previous results, exchanging time for space.
[src:rosetta-code/fibonacci-sequence-p06] Also, in the case of supplying both a function implementation and a predicate implementation, one of the two would be implemented in terms of the other.
[src:rosetta-code/fibonacci-sequence-p06] Examples of this are given as comments below.
